        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2016-06-20 17:00:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\nThis osd and osp xattr cache code is almost the same, actually, there are quite a lot code can be shared between osd/osp, and even between osd-ldiskfs/osd-zfs, it probably makes sense to pull out of these codes and create a common library.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "32f9d31fcc17b206d7b865ad133351d1f337e7a8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2016-06-20 17:03:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nDi, in osd-zfs/ we reuse dmu's cache (nvlist) which is mandatory for SA.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "c5a7bdafe573f73e648e6e5129f861c4cd9ce46c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2016-06-23 17:28:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\noh, thanks for the information.\nBut for osd-zfs/osd-ldiskfs, there are still some codes which can be shared, like fid/fld related stuff. And for xattr cache, at least the code between osp/osd-ldiskfs can be shared.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
